# Design Documentation: Dot Matrix Calendar Widget
## Based on PRD v1.0

---

## 1. Design System Overview

### 1.1 Visual Identity

**Design Philosophy:** Minimalist â€¢ Bold Typography â€¢ Dot Matrix Aesthetic â€¢ Premium Feel

**Core Principles:**
- **Simplicity First:** Remove all non-essential elements
- **Typography as Hero:** Large, bold numbers dominate the layout
- **Dot Language:** Consistent circular dot representation across all interfaces
- **Spatial Breathing:** Generous whitespace for visual calm
- **Tactile Clarity:** Clear visual feedback for all interactions

---

## 2. Widget Design Specifications

### 2.1 Month View Widget (Primary Reference from Image)

#### 2.1.1 Layout Structure

```
â”Œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”
â”‚  11                              Tue    â”‚  â† Header Section (96dp height)
â”‚  FEBRUARY                              â”‚
â”‚  2025                                  â”‚
â”‚                                        â”‚
â”‚  M   T   W   T   F   S   S            â”‚  â† Week Headers (24dp height)
â”‚                                        â”‚
â”‚  â—   â—   â—   â—   â—   â—   â—            â”‚  â† Week 1
â”‚  â—   â—   â—  [â—]  â—   â—   â—            â”‚  â† Week 2 (current day highlighted)
â”‚  â—   â—   â—   â—   â—‹   â—‹   â—‹            â”‚  â† Week 3 (future days lighter)
â”‚  â—‹   â—‹   â—‹   â—‹   â—‹   â—‹   â—‹            â”‚  â† Week 4 (future days)
â”‚                                        â”‚
â””â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”˜
```

#### 2.1.2 Precise Measurements

**Widget Canvas:**
- Recommended size: 4Ã—4 grid cells (approximately 360dp Ã— 360dp on standard density)
- Minimum size: 3Ã—3 grid cells (270dp Ã— 270dp)
- Padding: 16dp all sides

**Header Section:**
- Date Number ("11"): 72sp, Font: Sans-serif Black/Heavy
- Month ("FEBRUARY"): 14sp, Font: Sans-serif Medium, Letter-spacing: 0.8sp, All caps
- Year ("2025"): 12sp, Font: Sans-serif Regular, Opacity: 60%
- Day Name ("Tue"): 14sp, Font: Sans-serif Medium, Aligned right

**Week Day Headers:**
- Font Size: 10sp
- Font: Sans-serif Medium
- Color: #666666 (40% opacity of primary text)
- Letter-spacing: 0.5sp
- Height: 24dp
- Margin top: 12dp from header

**Dot Grid:**
- Dot Size: 32dp diameter (default, user-adjustable 24-48dp range)
- Dot Spacing: 8dp between centers (adjustable 4-16dp)
- Grid: 7 columns Ã— 5-6 rows
- Alignment: Center-aligned within widget bounds

#### 2.1.3 Color Specifications (from Image Analysis)

**Light Mode (Classic Light Theme):**

| Element | Color | Usage |
|---------|-------|-------|
| Background | #F5F5F5 | Widget canvas |
| Primary Text (Date) | #1A1A1A | Large date number |
| Secondary Text | #666666 | Month, year, day name |
| Completed Days (Past) | #1A1A1A | Filled dots |
| Current Day | #FF6B35 | Orange accent dot |
| Future Days | #D9D9D9 | Light gray unfilled dots |
| Week Headers | #999999 | Day initials |

**Typography Scale:**
```css
/* Typographic System */
--font-display: 72sp;      /* Date number */
--font-title: 14sp;        /* Month name */
--font-subtitle: 12sp;     /* Year, metadata */
--font-label: 10sp;        /* Week headers */
--font-caption: 8sp;       /* Small labels */

/* Font Weights */
--weight-black: 900;       /* Date number */
--weight-bold: 700;        /* Not used in this design */
--weight-medium: 500;      /* Month, day name */
--weight-regular: 400;     /* Year, labels */
```

#### 2.1.4 Dot States & Visual Treatment

**Dot Appearance Matrix:**

| State | Visual Treatment | Color | Opacity | Use Case |
|-------|------------------|-------|---------|----------|
| **Past Day** | Solid filled circle | #1A1A1A | 100% | Days already passed |
| **Current Day** | Solid filled circle | #FF6B35 | 100% | Today (accent color) |
| **Future Day** | Outlined or filled light | #D9D9D9 | 40% | Upcoming days |
| **Empty Space** | Invisible/Not rendered | N/A | 0% | Days not in month |
| **Emoji Day** | Emoji character | Color varies | 100% | User-marked special days |

**Dot Rendering Details:**
```kotlin
// Dot drawing specifications
data class DotStyle(
    val diameter: Float = 32f.dp,     // Default size
    val strokeWidth: Float = 2f.dp,   // For outlined dots
    val cornerRadius: Float = 16f.dp  // Full circle (50% of diameter)
)

// Visual states
sealed class DotState {
    object Past : DotState()          // Filled black
    object Current : DotState()       // Filled orange
    object Future : DotState()        // Light gray
    data class Emoji(val emoji: String) : DotState()  // Emoji overlay
}
```

---

### 2.2 Current Day Highlight Treatment

**From Image Analysis:** The current day (11) uses an **orange accent color** (#FF6B35) that stands out clearly from the black past days and light gray future days.

**Highlight Specifications:**

**Option A: Solid Fill (Shown in Image)**
```
Current Day Dot:
- Fill: #FF6B35 (orange)
- Size: Same as other dots (32dp)
- No additional visual effects
- Clean, minimal approach
```

**Option B: Enhanced Visibility (Alternative)**
```
Current Day Dot:
- Fill: #FF6B35
- Ring/Stroke: 2dp, #FF6B35 at 30% opacity
- Subtle glow: 4dp blur radius (optional, Pro feature)
- Scale: 1.1x size (35.2dp) for emphasis
```

**Recommended:** Use Option A (solid fill) for MVP to match the clean aesthetic shown in the reference image.

---

